Distribution. Circumpolar from New England , the Canadian Archipelago, over Greenland , Iceland , the Barents Sea, White Sea, Kara Sea, Laptev Sea to the east Siberian Seas, down to Japan , British Columbia (
Schiøtte 1998
;
Kantor & Sysoev 2006
). In Norway along the entire coastline; British Isles southwards to the Mediterranean Sea and the Canary Islands (
Thompson 1988
;
Poppe & Goto 1991
;
Schiøtte 1998
;
Høisaeter et al . 2001
;
Sneli et al . 2005
).
